https://docs.docker.com/engine/security/rootless/#limiting-resources

## Podman
Ubuntu's version of Podman is very old. Install a newer version like so:

```
sudo mkdir -p /etc/apt/keyrings

# Debian Testing/Bookworm
curl -fsSL https://download.opensuse.org/repositories/devel:kubic:libcontainers:unstable/Debian_Testing/Release.key \
  | gpg --dearmor \
  | sudo tee /etc/apt/keyrings/devel_kubic_libcontainers_unstable.gpg > /dev/null
echo \
  "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/devel_kubic_libcontainers_unstable.gpg]\
    https://download.opensuse.org/repositories/devel:kubic:libcontainers:unstable/Debian_Testing/ /" \
  | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/devel:kubic:libcontainers:unstable.list > /dev/null

sudo apt update
sudo apt -y upgrade
sudo apt -y install podman podman-docker libgpgme11-dev libyajl2 libslirp0
```

# Silence warnings about `docker` being an alias for `podman` in this setup
sudo touch /etc/containers/nodocker
echo 'unqualified-search-registries = ["docker.io"]' | sudo tee -a /etc/containers/registries.conf


podman system reset
# Created by traefik container
sudo rm /var/run/docker.sock


